releases.name: v2.6.1
releases.body: Fixed a bug (#143) that could cause issues when changing axis types.

releases.name: v2.6.0
releases.body:
Safety Outlier Explorer v2.6.0 addresses overplotting by identifying overlapping points on hover and on click.  This new feature exposes the number of overlapping points underneath the mouse in the point's tooltip, and on click adds a note beneath the chart with a list of participants associated with the overlapping points:

![overlapping-points](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5428548/63535459-79b27380-c4df-11e9-9d7b-ea705f5be7b9.png)

View a full list of resolved issues [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-outlier-explorer/issues?utf8=✓&q=is%3Aissue+milestone%3Av2.6.0+).

releases.name: v2.5.5
releases.body: Adds support for new [`participantsSelected` event](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-outlier-explorer/wiki/API#participantsselected).

releases.name: v2.5.4
releases.body: Safety Outlier Explorer v2.5.4 makes `array` settings (`filters`, `details`, and `tooltip_cols`) more permissive by allowing a string argument in addition to an array of length 1.

releases.name: v2.5.3
releases.body: Safety Outlier Explorer v2.5.3 fixes a bug that arises when the data has a range of zero.

releases.name: v2.5.2
releases.body: Safety Outlier Explorer v2.5.2 updates the CDN of the examples in /test-page to cdn.jsdelivr.net.

releases.name: v2.5.1
releases.body: Added a [second example](http://rhoinc.github.io/safety-outlier-explorer/test-page/hyslaw/) using Hy's Law data

releases.name: v2.5.0
releases.body:
- Displays non-numeric record warnings to user.
- Y-axis limit controls adjust dynamically based on range of data.
- Various bug fixes and improvements. Full list [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-outlier-explorer/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue+milestone%3Av2.5.0+).

releases.name: v2.4.0
releases.body: Safety Outlier Explorer v.2.4.0 adds a participant dropdown to the small multiples, cycles overlapping points on click, and adds support for custom tooltips.  View a full list of resolved issues [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-outlier-explorer/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue+milestone%3Av2.4.0+).

releases.name: v2.3.0
releases.body: Safety Outlier Explorer v2.3.0 adds a visual normal range to the chart and improves its aesthetics.  View a full list of resolved issues [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-outlier-explorer/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue+milestone%3Av2.3.0+).

releases.name: v2.2.3
releases.body: safety-outlier-explorer v2.2.3 updates the control label of custom controls from _control-label_ to _wc-control-label_ to avoid css conflicts with bootstrap.

releases.name: v2.2.2
releases.body: v2.2.2 fixes a bug in the script that parses the settings schema and builds the configuration page in the wiki.  No source code files were modified.

releases.name: v2.2.1
releases.body: Technical difficulties with `npm publish` required an updated patch release.

releases.name: v2.2.0
releases.body: safety-outlier-explorer v2.2.0 adds a settings schema, a data-driven visit order, and controls that display and hide unscheduled visits and visits without data.  The full list of issues is available [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-outlier-explorer/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue+milestone%3Av2.2.0+).

releases.name: v2.1.1
releases.body: Fixes bug in label order when filters are added to the chart. #64

releases.name: v2.1.0
releases.body: This release adds a set of y-axis domain controls because users complained about outliers obscuring the rest of the data.

releases.name: v2.0.3
releases.body:
- Added support for time_col.order #53 
- Fixed a bug where time points could be hidden dropped from small multiples in certain situations #54

releases.name: v2.0.2
releases.body: Fix a bug that could cause duplicate controls in certain frameworks #51

releases.name: v2.0.1
releases.body: Minor update so that filters with 0 or 1 levels no longer render. (#46)

releases.name: v2.0.0
releases.body: Version 2.0.0 of the Safety Outlier Explorer represents a major refactor, and includes many bug fixes and performance improvements. The overall framework using [webcharts-boilerplate](https://github.com/RhoInc/webcharts-wrapper-boilerplate) is still in place, but the secondary build creating a react framework has been removed, and several [configuration options](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-outlier-explorer/wiki/Configuration) have been simplified, breaking backwards compatibility. A full list of resolved issues is available [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-outlier-explorer/milestone/1?closed=1).

- A wiki has been added with details regarding chart configuration, links to examples and data guidelines.

releases.name: v1.1.0
releases.body: Added ability to rotate axis ticks to avoid overlap.

This is the initial release of the Test Results Outlier Explorer. This interactive tool allows users to compare lab and vital sign data over time to search for values that fall outside of expected ranges.

issues.title: Handle unexpected visits systematically
issues.body:
Depending on how unscheduled visits are displayed on the x-axis, the chart can have some unintended behavior.

(See related issue for Results Over Time: https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-results-over-time/issues/43)

If visits are displayed purely chronologically, the challenge is that you end up creating a new event type that shows up in the middle of the data, but for only a small number of data points.  See example of visits 2.1 and 4.1 below:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10886203/34954341-08e08bfa-f9ee-11e7-8ba5-b5fa2dd45047.png)

Our primary medical monitor user has proposed that to fix this, we sort all Unscheduled visits to the far right end of the chart, where they are still visible, but they don't interfere with seeing the data flow through expected visits.  The problem here is that the chart sometimes connects these points in a non-linear way:
![example2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10886203/34954556-d23ae194-f9ee-11e7-9c94-9aaf9f0b5146.jpg)

Proposed solutions:
1. Retain visits in numerical order, but create a toggle that lets the user "Hide unscheduled visits"
2. Force the chart to connect the dots in the same order as the axis is drawn

# Test notes
Test out the new "Visits without data" and "Unscheduled visits" controls in CAT with the safetyData/ADBDS.csv data file (not safetyData-queries/ADBDS.csv).

Confirm that:

* Unscheduled Visits and Visits with no data are shown/hidden when the toggle changes.
* Change measure to "Alkaline Phosphatase (ALP)" and confirm that visits with no data are shown/hidden when the toggle changes.
* Test with the above with groups active (settings: {groups:["RACE"]})
* Unscheduled visits are shown on initial load with {"unscheduled_visits":true}
* Visits with no data are shown on initial load with {"visits_without_data": false}
* Only the visits are hidden/shown when explicitly specified using {unscheduled_visit_values:["Unscheduled 2.1","Screening"]}
